"{\n  \"correct\": \"no\",\n  \"explanation\": \"The code is incorrect because it does not properly clear the current figure after saving it. This will cause all subsequent scatterplots to be drawn on top of the previous ones, resulting in an incorrect plot. Matplotlib's pyplot API uses a concept of a 'current figure', which is the figure that is currently being drawn to. When you call plt.savefig(), it saves the current figure. However, when you call sns.scatterplot() again, it does not automatically create a new figure; instead, it draws to the current figure. To fix this, you should call plt.clf() after saving the figure to clear the current figure.\",\n  \"patch\": \"18a19\\n> plt.clf()\\n\"\n}"